<div class="box-text">
<p>New research revealing the extent of the physical, emotional, and social burden of X-linked  hypophosphataemia (XLH) on Australian patients<sup>1</sup> been released to mark Rare Disease Day (Monday, 28 February).</p>
<p>The first-ever, Australia-based research from XLH Australia Incorporated (in collaboration with Kyowa Kirin Australia) aims to increase understanding of what it is like to live with the rare genetic disease.<sup>1</sup></p>
<p>See the key findings the infographic below.</p>
